of Arizona's separation order

28:38.891 --> 28:40.936
do not suffer

28:40.980 --> 28:42.111
irreparable harm.

28:42.155 --> 28:43.896
Judge, the ACLU is
a private litigant,

28:43.939 --> 28:46.550
so the case
is not precisely on point.

28:46.594 --> 28:48.248
That is true.And this court
is not bound

28:48.291 --> 28:50.729
by another federal
appellate court's judgment.

28:50.772 --> 28:52.382
Also true.

28:52.426 --> 28:56.125
But the opinion adjudicated
nearly identical facts.

28:56.169 --> 28:58.127
I consider that
persuasive authority

28:58.171 --> 28:59.389
and a judgment

28:59.433 --> 29:02.784
I am not inclined to contravene.

29:02.828 --> 29:04.917
Wha...
Uh, so...

29:04.960 --> 29:07.876
th-that's it?

29:07.920 --> 29:09.965
An inadvertent
legal wire-crossing

29:10.009 --> 29:12.881
means all those kids

29:12.925 --> 29:14.927
have to remain separated
from their parents?

29:14.970 --> 29:16.711
I'm afraid so.

29:16.755 --> 29:19.192
You'll have to let your suit
wend its way through the system,

29:19.235 --> 29:22.021
Mr. Jackson.

29:22.064 --> 29:22.891
MIKE:
Look at this.

29:22.935 --> 29:24.110
A sign from the gods.Hey.

29:24.153 --> 29:25.111
I am trolling for favors,

29:25.154 --> 29:26.460
and here you are.
I also need

29:26.503 --> 29:28.462
to hit up Russell
Jackson as well.

29:28.505 --> 29:30.551
This might not be
the best time.
Yeah, I heard.

29:30.594 --> 29:32.118
Bit of an ouch-y in court.

29:32.161 --> 29:34.642
How else would
you describe it?Oh, I don't know, Mike,

29:34.685 --> 29:36.687
maybe sensitively.Mm.

29:36.731 --> 29:38.428
What favors
are you here for?

29:38.472 --> 29:40.822
I need recommendation letters
for my kid's super-elitist,

29:40.866 --> 29:43.085
beyond-his-intellectual-
capacity private school.

29:43.129 --> 29:45.000
Mike, do you really want

29:45.044 --> 29:48.264
to send your son to a school
that he is not suited for?

29:48.308 --> 29:49.788
100%. So can I count on you?

29:49.831 --> 29:52.486
Well, it's a hell of a day
to be asking for a favor

29:52.529 --> 29:53.835
for your privileged kid.

29:55.271 --> 29:57.665
[sighs] All right,
send me his application

29:57.708 --> 29:59.232
and his ess...

29:59.275 --> 30:00.668
No promises.

30:00.711 --> 30:03.540
Fine. Look, I also got
the invite to your vow thing.

30:03.584 --> 30:05.934
Nice optics. I can't believe
I didn't think of it myself.

30:05.978 --> 30:08.589
I reached out
to thevideographer...No publicity.

30:08.632 --> 30:10.330
No publicity.
Just a videographer.

30:10.373 --> 30:12.506
Very discreet drones.
You won't even hear them.

30:12.549 --> 30:15.030
Mike, this is a personal
and private event.

30:15.074 --> 30:16.640
No politics.

30:16.684 --> 30:18.077
No angles.
Hey, look,

30:18.120 --> 30:19.600
I have been
dissecting the polls,

30:19.643 --> 30:21.080
and while you have
broad support--

30:21.123 --> 30:22.690
no pun intended--
you lack voter intensity.

30:22.733 --> 30:24.692
People like you,
but they don't love you.

30:24.735 --> 30:26.520
Do you know what
could change that?

30:26.563 --> 30:28.522
The sight of you
in a wedding dress.

30:28.565 --> 30:31.394
America would
go macadamia.
As in nuts.

30:31.438 --> 30:34.528
No, no, I put it together.
The answer's still no.[stammering]

30:34.571 --> 30:35.921
Okay, let's just get
the footage,

30:35.964 --> 30:37.966
and then we'll
sort it out in post.

30:38.010 --> 30:40.577
President Zaragoza,
I agree this is a travesty.

30:40.621 --> 30:43.232
Arizona won't even let
Mexican diplomats in

30:43.276 --> 30:46.018
to visit our citizens.That's unacceptable,
and we will do everything

30:46.061 --> 30:48.716
in our power to help your people
gain access as soon as possible.

30:48.759 --> 30:52.154
I'm afraid
until this outrage is ended

30:52.198 --> 30:53.939
it is not just
our border security deal

30:53.982 --> 30:55.505
that is off the table.

30:55.549 --> 30:58.160
Our entire relationship
is at stake.

30:58.204 --> 30:59.292
Mario...

30:59.335 --> 31:01.250
I am sorry.

31:01.294 --> 31:04.123
He's right.

31:04.166 --> 31:07.039
I'd have reacted
the same way.

31:07.082 --> 31:10.694
So, our border security deal
is dead.

31:11.521 --> 31:13.610
And our vital trade agreements
and a million others

31:13.654 --> 31:16.309
with our neighbors to
the south are threatened.

31:16.352 --> 31:18.050
And every hour that passes

31:18.093 --> 31:19.921
with kids separated
from their parents

31:19.965 --> 31:22.097
lowers our standing
in the world.

31:22.141 --> 31:24.491
Courts can't help us,
Congress won't,

31:24.534 --> 31:27.886
and we are powerless
to do a damn thing about it.

31:27.929 --> 31:30.279
Did I miss anything?

31:30.323 --> 31:31.933
HENRY:
Maybe one.

31:31.977 --> 31:33.239
Lao-tzu said:

31:33.282 --> 31:36.938
"An ant on the move
does more than a dozing ox."

31:38.853 --> 31:40.811
What the hell does that mean?If you can't do
everything,

31:40.855 --> 31:41.900
at least do something.

31:41.943 --> 31:43.379
Keep moving
in the right direction.

31:43.423 --> 31:46.252
What do you have in mind, Henry?Go down there,

31:46.295 --> 31:47.470
Mr. President.

31:47.514 --> 31:48.950
Walk those Mexican officials

31:48.994 --> 31:50.909
into the detention
center yourself.

31:50.952 --> 31:52.693
RUSSELL:
Whoa. Whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa.

31:52.736 --> 31:55.043
That... could open us up
to accusations

31:55.087 --> 31:57.045
of infringing on states' rights.

31:57.089 --> 31:58.307
That is... that is

31:58.351 --> 32:01.354
practically asking
for a constitutional crisis.

32:01.397 --> 32:04.226
Look, I-I am as disgusted
as any of you,

32:04.270 --> 32:06.402
but I will throw my body

32:06.446 --> 32:08.970
in front of that.Well, then I'll do it.

32:09.014 --> 32:10.406
Did you hear what I just said?

32:10.450 --> 32:12.408
Yes, and I'm not the president.

32:12.452 --> 32:15.890
You might be ensuring
that you never will be.

32:15.934 --> 32:18.501
It's-it's domestic interference.

32:18.545 --> 32:22.157
I'd be the Secretary of State
working with our Mexican allies

32:22.201 --> 32:24.029
to visit their own citizens.

32:24.072 --> 32:26.727
HENRY:
Advocating for foreign
dignitaries on our soil--

32:26.770 --> 32:28.250
it's not only
a moral imperative,

32:28.294 --> 32:30.426
it's a diplomatic
one, as well.

32:30.470 --> 32:33.995
Sounds very
Secretary-of-Statey to me.

32:34.039 --> 32:37.172
Mr. President, Governor
Barker's intentionally

32:37.216 --> 32:40.349
provocative policy
deserves to be met

32:40.393 --> 32:43.918
with an equally
provocative response.

32:51.143 --> 32:52.971
MAN:
Madam Secretary?Reunite the families!

32:53.014 --> 32:57.540
KAT: Well, it's not
exactly the Hilton.

32:57.584 --> 32:58.977
Well, it would be different

32:59.020 --> 33:00.543
if their parents
were with them.

33:00.587 --> 33:01.849
Mm.

33:01.892 --> 33:03.068
Oh, God, this isn't
gonna be easy.

33:03.111 --> 33:04.504
Nope, it's not, ma'am,
but you know what?

33:04.547 --> 33:06.506
There's no other place
I would rather be.

33:06.549 --> 33:08.508
PROTESTORS [chanting]:
Reunite the families!

33:08.551 --> 33:10.423
You know, the second
we're done here,

33:10.466 --> 33:12.294
feel free to go
see your dad.

33:12.338 --> 33:13.643
How far away
is he again?

33:13.687 --> 33:15.210
Oh, Dad's a couple hours
in Aguila.

33:15.254 --> 33:17.299
Thank you, but I'll probably
take a rain check.

33:17.343 --> 33:18.909
Madam Secretary.

33:18.953 --> 33:21.260
Ambassador Lopez,
you know Kat Sandoval.

33:21.303 --> 33:22.652
[speaking Spanish]

33:22.696 --> 33:25.220
I am here at the direction
of President Zaragoza

33:25.264 --> 33:27.222
to look after the
interests of my citizens.

33:27.266 --> 33:29.398
Of course.

33:29.442 --> 33:32.010
Well, let's do this.

33:32.053 --> 33:34.360
All right.

33:34.403 --> 33:37.798
Good afternoon...
Officer Keegan.

33:37.841 --> 33:39.669
I'm Elizabeth McCord.

33:39.713 --> 33:43.108
This is Mexican Ambassador
Rafael Lopez.

33:43.151 --> 33:44.283
Well, how are you today?

33:44.326 --> 33:45.371
I'm okay, ma'am,

33:45.414 --> 33:47.112
but I'm afraid...That's great.

33:47.155 --> 33:50.289
I'm here to escort the
ambassador inside the facility

33:50.332 --> 33:52.682
so that he can check
on his citizens.

33:52.726 --> 33:55.424
I'm afraid I'm not authorized
to allow that, ma'am.

33:55.468 --> 33:58.297
I wasn't clear
about that, either, and...

33:58.340 --> 34:00.603
This is Kat Sandoval,
my policy advisor.

34:00.647 --> 34:02.475
Kat, can you help us out here?

34:02.518 --> 34:04.216
Hey there, Officer Keegan.

34:04.259 --> 34:06.522
It's totally understandable that
you wouldn't be up to speed,

34:06.566 --> 34:08.307
given the different state
and federal laws.

34:08.350 --> 34:11.484
It can be a little bit,
you know-- "Aah!"-- confusing.

34:11.527 --> 34:14.835
However, under title 22
USC section 26-51,

34:14.878 --> 34:17.403
"Foreign Nationals on U.S.
Soil," you must yield

34:17.446 --> 34:19.274
and allow entry
immediately.

34:19.318 --> 34:20.971
Huh.

34:21.015 --> 34:23.061
Yeah, and it literally
says, "immediately."

34:23.104 --> 34:24.497
[static]

34:24.540 --> 34:26.107
Hey, Miller?

34:26.151 --> 34:27.456
I don't think we want to get

34:27.500 --> 34:29.284
any of our bosses involved.Yeah.

34:29.328 --> 34:32.374
Right,
Officer Keegan?

34:32.418 --> 34:34.420
Um...

34:34.463 --> 34:36.422
You'll just need
to surrender your phones.

34:36.465 --> 34:38.380
Great. Thank you.Of course.

34:39.468 --> 34:41.122
[knocking]

34:41.166 --> 34:43.298
Hey.
Hey.

34:43.342 --> 34:45.387
Here's a blast from your past.

34:45.431 --> 34:47.041
What are you doing here?

34:47.085 --> 34:48.956
Okay, maybe not my
strongest entrance,

34:48.999 --> 34:51.393
but I do come
bearing gifts.

34:51.437 --> 34:54.440
I realize I'm a little
late with the baby present.

34:54.483 --> 34:56.964
What is he,
five months now?
She.

34:57.007 --> 34:58.400
And a year.
Oh.

34:58.444 --> 35:02.448
Wow. Uh, well, then I guess
it's a birthday present.

35:02.491 --> 35:04.841
And here's a little something

35:04.885 --> 35:06.539
I brought for Jay.Mm-hmm.

35:06.582 --> 35:08.758
I feel so bad about
what happened.

35:08.802 --> 35:11.239
I'm not sure he believed
I didn't do it on purpose,

35:11.283 --> 35:13.241
but I-I swear, I am
not a good enough

35:13.285 --> 35:14.503
defensive player
to make that happen.

35:14.547 --> 35:16.201
Yeah, I'm not entirely
in the loop on this,

35:16.244 --> 35:17.550
and I like it that way.

35:17.593 --> 35:19.465
Fair enough.

35:19.508 --> 35:22.337
It's just that earlier I was
asking about the possibility

35:22.381 --> 35:24.122
of a sit-down
with the secretary, and ...

35:24.165 --> 35:26.036
Look, it's kind of
a busy day around here,

35:26.080 --> 35:28.561
and y-you're just gonna have
to find someone else to lobby.

35:28.604 --> 35:33.000
Well, can you just make
sure he gets this then?

35:33.043 --> 35:34.610
It, uh, has some
goodies in there

35:34.654 --> 35:35.916
that'll help
with the pain.

35:35.959 --> 35:38.310
Did you seriously bring
a controlled substance

35:38.353 --> 35:39.528
into the State Department?

35:39.572 --> 35:40.703
Not for the first time,
if you'll recall.

35:41.139 --> 35:43.576
You know,
when-when there was a lockdown,

35:43.619 --> 35:45.447
and I got Matt high,
and I found out

35:45.491 --> 35:47.319
that you were cheating
on me with him, and...

35:47.362 --> 35:49.451
Okay, I will.
I will get this to Jay.

35:49.495 --> 35:51.453
And I will tell him
whatever it is I remember

35:51.497 --> 35:52.367
of what you just said.

35:52.411 --> 35:54.108
You're a peach.

35:54.152 --> 35:56.458
But... you-you know, like,
a really smart one.

35:56.502 --> 35:57.894
Mm.I'm sorry.

35:57.938 --> 35:59.200
Maybe I shouldn't have gone
with a stone fruit.

35:59.244 --> 36:00.810
It... Uh...

36:00.854 --> 36:03.161
All-all right, yeah.

36:05.946 --> 36:08.035
[door closes loudly,
lights buzzing]

36:13.345 --> 36:15.912
In here.

36:18.959 --> 36:20.743
Oh, my God.

36:20.787 --> 36:24.138
Madre, Madre, quiero mi madre.

36:24.182 --> 36:25.226
[indistinct chatter]

36:25.270 --> 36:27.750
How is this possible?

36:27.794 --> 36:30.100
The great United States
of America.

36:36.759 --> 36:38.805
[children crying,
indistinct chatter]

36:43.462 --> 36:45.464
[crying and chatter continue]

36:52.471 --> 36:56.649
Hey, excuse me?

36:56.692 --> 36:59.652
Are you gonna change
that boy's diaper?

36:59.695 --> 37:02.089
I mean, I'm assuming
he has one.

37:02.132 --> 37:04.439
Child aides make rounds
every three hours.

37:04.483 --> 37:06.833
Three hours.

37:09.357 --> 37:11.533
So you're just gonna
leave him like that?

37:11.577 --> 37:14.188
'Cause, I mean, where are his
clothes? I'll change him myself.

37:14.232 --> 37:15.189
Ma'am, that's
not procedure.

37:15.233 --> 37:16.712
I don't care about procedure.

37:16.756 --> 37:18.627
Look at him.

37:27.157 --> 37:29.159
Hola.

37:37.907 --> 37:40.083
Daniel.

37:40.127 --> 37:41.955
Daniel.

37:53.706 --> 37:55.708
Daniel, no.

38:07.154 --> 38:08.590
[buzzer sounds]

38:08.634 --> 38:09.983
RICHARD: Secretary
Elizabeth McCord,

38:10.026 --> 38:14.117
you are trespassing
on Arizona state property.

38:14.161 --> 38:16.250
Am I really?

38:16.294 --> 38:18.644
You tricked your way in here,

38:18.687 --> 38:21.168
grandstanding
for the press

38:21.211 --> 38:24.519
on your self-promotion tour,
but you are a long way

38:24.563 --> 38:26.869
from the federal swamp
you call home.

38:29.742 --> 38:33.180
Well, Governor,
if Washington, D.C. is a swamp,

38:33.223 --> 38:36.792
what's this?

38:36.836 --> 38:39.012
It's none of your business
is what it is.

38:39.055 --> 38:40.709
And there's a sheriff out front

38:40.753 --> 38:42.537
with a warrant
for your arrest.

38:42.581 --> 38:46.585
Is he going to arrest
Ambassador Lopez, as well?

38:46.628 --> 38:48.587
Mr. Ambassador,
I'm sorry you got dragged

38:48.630 --> 38:50.371
into Madam Secretary's

38:50.415 --> 38:51.503
little publicity stunt.

38:51.546 --> 38:53.679
I didn't get dragged
into anything.

38:53.722 --> 38:56.377
My government demands these
innocent children get reunited

38:56.421 --> 38:58.684
with their parents immediately.

38:58.727 --> 39:02.035
Your government has
no authority here, sir.

39:02.078 --> 39:04.429
Neither does yours, ma'am.

39:04.472 --> 39:08.868
I think the ambassador's demand
is on humanitarian grounds.

39:08.911 --> 39:11.174
I don't care
if it's on grounds of coffee.

39:11.218 --> 39:13.220
This is my state and my rules.

39:13.263 --> 39:17.746
Lucky for you, I'm feeling
charitable today.

39:17.790 --> 39:20.532
Y'all can exit peaceably

39:20.575 --> 39:22.621
through the back
without talking to any press,

39:22.664 --> 39:25.058
and I'll let you leave
this state without incident.

39:25.101 --> 39:26.799
[laughs]
Without incident?

39:26.842 --> 39:28.975
Okay.

39:29.018 --> 39:31.107
Look around, Governor.

39:31.151 --> 39:33.109
We passed that.

39:33.153 --> 39:35.111
I suggest you get moving

39:35.155 --> 39:38.419
before I invite the good sheriff
in here to come get you.

39:38.463 --> 39:40.378
[child crying]

39:42.467 --> 39:46.993
Did you think you can
intimidate me or shut me up?

39:51.998 --> 39:53.434
Don't test Arizona justice,
ma'am.

39:53.478 --> 39:54.653
[buzzer sounding]

39:54.696 --> 39:56.263
FATHER DINARDO:
Saint Francis said,

39:56.306 --> 39:58.352
"All the darkness in the world
cannot extinguish the light

39:58.396 --> 39:59.875
of a single candle."MAN: That's right!

39:59.919 --> 40:02.443
If it took a visit
from the Secretary of State

40:02.487 --> 40:05.359
to shine a light on the darkness
inside this building,

40:05.403 --> 40:07.361
then praise the Lord
for sending her.

40:07.405 --> 40:09.450
And God bless
and protect those children,

40:09.494 --> 40:11.974
our little brothers and sisters
in the Lord's kingdom.

40:12.018 --> 40:13.976
Why did you come to Arizona,
Madam Secretary?

40:14.020 --> 40:16.065
What did you see in there?Are the children
being mistreated?

40:16.109 --> 40:17.632
MAN: What kind of care
do they have in there?

40:17.676 --> 40:19.199
MAN 2:
What do you hope to prove?

40:19.242 --> 40:21.201
I came here to see for myself

40:21.244 --> 40:24.465
and to help Ambassador Lopez see

40:24.509 --> 40:26.380
what's going on
behind these walls.

40:26.424 --> 40:30.340
What I saw is an affront
to decency

40:30.384 --> 40:35.737
and an assault
on our country's core values.

40:35.781 --> 40:39.393
Children separated
from their parents,

40:39.437 --> 40:44.050
in cages, crying, terrified,

40:44.093 --> 40:46.835
lacking basic care.

40:46.879 --> 40:49.751
[phone ringing]

40:49.795 --> 40:51.710
And the governor believes
it's a deterrent.

40:51.753 --> 40:53.320
It'll keep others...Hi.

40:53.363 --> 40:54.321
Are you seeing this?

40:54.364 --> 40:55.365
HENRY:
Yup.

40:55.409 --> 40:57.106
That's your mom.

40:57.150 --> 40:59.544
[siren blaring]But it is child abuse,

40:59.587 --> 41:01.284
plain and simple.Ma'am?

41:01.328 --> 41:03.156
WOMAN:
Yes!
No deterrent

41:03.199 --> 41:07.421
is worth trading
our humanity.
That's enough.

41:07.465 --> 41:09.815
No policy, no
matter its goal,

41:09.858 --> 41:12.252
is worth lowering
our moral standing

41:12.295 --> 41:14.210
in the world.
RICHARD:
All right.

41:14.254 --> 41:16.648
Nothing can justify
harming children.

41:16.691 --> 41:18.388
Ma'am, you are
on state property.

41:18.432 --> 41:20.826
And the governor
wants me to shut up.

41:20.869 --> 41:22.480
Yes.

41:22.523 --> 41:25.308
But I won't, because
what he's doing

41:25.352 --> 41:27.702
is immoral and
un-American,

41:27.746 --> 41:31.140
and every American
needs to know about it.

41:31.184 --> 41:32.838
SHERIFF:
Elizabeth McCord,

41:32.881 --> 41:34.927
you are under arrest

41:34.970 --> 41:36.972
for criminal trespass
in the first degree

41:37.016 --> 41:38.583
in violation of section 13...No.

41:38.626 --> 41:41.673
No! No! ...-1504.

41:41.716 --> 41:43.849
[overlapping shouting]

41:43.892 --> 41:45.720
Well...

41:45.764 --> 41:48.506
if desperate asylum-seekers

41:48.549 --> 41:51.030
aren't free from being

41:51.073 --> 41:53.336
detained unfairly

41:53.380 --> 41:55.338
in this state,

41:55.382 --> 41:57.558
why should I?

41:57.602 --> 41:59.473
Take her in, Trooper.

41:59.517 --> 42:00.561
Please.

42:00.605 --> 42:03.346
It's okay, Jared.
It's okay.

42:03.390 --> 42:05.958
[indistinct,
overlapping shouting]

42:06.001 --> 42:07.960
Officer Stevens.

42:08.003 --> 42:10.484
STEVENS:
Uh, if you could please
turn around and put your hands

42:10.528 --> 42:11.529
behind your back?

42:11.572 --> 42:13.008
Okay.

42:13.052 --> 42:16.403
I'm guessing this isn't how
you thought your day would go.

42:16.446 --> 42:17.535
STEVENS:
No, ma'am.

42:17.578 --> 42:18.448
SHERIFF:
Take the protestors, too.

42:18.492 --> 42:20.581
You're under arrest.

42:20.625 --> 42:23.932
[indistinct,
overlapping shouting]

42:23.976 --> 42:25.673
Has anything like this
ever happened before?

42:25.717 --> 42:27.370
HENRY:
Not in the United States.

42:27.414 --> 42:29.285
No. Not here.

42:29.329 --> 42:31.940
Never.

42:33.594 --> 42:35.596
PROTESTORS [chanting]:
Reunite families!

42:35.640 --> 42:37.555
Okay.Reunite families!

42:37.598 --> 42:40.253
[chanting continues]

